subproject.description:
The project is one of three components of Energy Efficiency programme, financed by the Austrian Development Cooperation, and aims in enabling the environment for mitigating climate change in the country through improved energy efficiency in the building sector and enhanced awareness and capacities of stakeholders involved in energy efficiency issues. 
The main outputs of the project are: 
1) national database on climate parameters per regions and a software for measuring energy consumption in buildings on local level; 
2) an inventory of public buildings nationwide; 
3) Energy Efficiency Programmes for three pilot municipalities; 
4)  investment–oriented energy efficient building programme; 5) Public awareness and knowledge about energy efficiency and energy saving measures in building sector.

